data_description: This table contains consolidated customer service metrics data for Mental Health Disorders (MHD) support operations. It includes monthly aggregated data across multiple customer interaction channels including IVR calls, chatbot interactions, and human agent tickets. Key data categories encompass call volumes (ivr_calls, bot_ticket_count), satisfaction metrics (bot_positive_response, agent_tickets_msat_received), feedback tracking (bot_total_responses, agent_tickets_feedback_received), and channel transfer metrics (agent_ticket_count_bot, bot_to_service_ticket_count). The table structure supports time-series analysis with monthly granularity and includes calculated ratios and percentages for performance measurement.

business_description: This table serves as the primary data source for customer care performance monitoring and reporting in the Mental Health Disorders support vertical. It enables business stakeholders to track customer service efficiency across different channels, measure customer satisfaction (MSAT scores), and analyze the effectiveness of bot-to-human escalation processes. The data supports operational decision-making regarding resource allocation between automated (bot) and human agent services, identification of service bottlenecks, and optimization of customer experience workflows. It's used for monthly performance reviews, trend analysis of customer service metrics, and strategic planning for customer care operations improvement.

data_description: This table contains daily aggregated data tracking pendency status for QR (Quick Response) and SB operations. It includes dimensions for categorizing pending items by days_bucket (time duration buckets), final_stage (ultimate status/stage), and substage (intermediate processing stages), with each record identified by an ID for counting purposes. The table appears to be a daily snapshot or aggregation that provides a comprehensive view of pending cases across different processing stages and time buckets.

business_description: This table supports Care Dashboard operations by enabling monitoring and management of pending cases or requests in QR and SB workflows. It allows business users to track how long items have been pending (via days_bucket), understand where items are stuck in the process (via final_stage and substage), and identify bottlenecks or areas requiring attention. The data is used for operational reporting, performance monitoring, and ensuring timely resolution of customer service or operational requests.
